<subSubSection id="C3485ED60971B22FEC95FC9F229E49C4" pageId="37" pageNumber="488" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0971B22FEC95FC9F24DF4974" blockId="37.[151,1437,835,1113]" box="[151,1236,835,861]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0971B22FEC95FC9F21294974" bold="true" box="[151,290,835,861]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Etymology:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0971B22FED2BFC9F21984974" authorityName="Cuvier" authorityYear="1828" box="[297,403,835,861]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ambassidae" genus="Ambassis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="37" pageNumber="488" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0971B22FED2BFC9F21984974" box="[297,403,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Ambassis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: derived from Greek, 
<emphasis id="B926D14F0971B22FEE8EFC9F22FB4974" box="[652,752,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">anabasis</emphasis>
= climbing up; 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0971B22FEF9EFC9F24414974" baseAuthorityName="Lacepede" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[924,1098,835,861]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ambassidae" genus="Ambassis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="37" pageNumber="488" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gymnocephalus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0971B22FEF9EFC9F24414974" box="[924,1098,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">gymnocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: short head.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0971B22FECC5FCBA221749A8" blockId="37.[151,1437,835,1113]" box="[199,540,870,897]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0971B22FECC5FCBA218C49A8" bold="true" box="[199,391,870,897]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Common name:</emphasis>
Bald Glassy.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0971B22FECC5FC57229E49C4" blockId="37.[151,1437,835,1113]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0971B22FECC5FC572145498C" bold="true" box="[199,334,907,933]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Taxonomy:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0971B22FED54FC572264498C" authorityName="Lacepede" authorityYear="1802" box="[342,623,907,933]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Lutjanidae" genus="Lutjanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="37" pageNumber="488" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gymnocephalus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0971B22FED54FC572264498C" box="[342,623,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Lutjanus gymnocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by Lacepède [B. G. E.] (ex Commerson) 1802:181, 216 [Histoire naturelle des poissons (Lacepède) v. 4] from Le grand Océan équinoxal or dans les parties de ce grand Océan voisines des tropiques” [Indo-Pacific].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3485ED60971B22FECC5FC2B246D4DDC" pageId="37" pageNumber="488" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0971B22FECC5FC2B220F4E38" blockId="37.[151,1437,835,1113]" box="[199,516,1015,1041]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0971B22FECC5FC2B21364E38" bold="true" box="[199,317,1015,1041]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">
<typeStatus id="54E9B3FF0971B22FECC5FC2B21334E38" box="[199,312,1015,1041]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Holotype</typeStatus>
:
</emphasis>
No types known.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0971B22FECC5FBC624244E70" blockId="37.[151,1437,835,1113]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0971B22FECC5FBC621404E1D" bold="true" box="[199,331,1050,1076]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Synonyms:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0971B22FED57FBC723254E1C" authority="Lacepede, 1801" authorityName="Lacepede" authorityYear="1801" box="[341,814,1051,1077]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Lutjanidae" genus="Lutianus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="37" pageNumber="488" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gymnocephalus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0971B22FED57FBC722654E1C" box="[341,622,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Lutianus gymnocephalus</emphasis>
Lacepede, 1801
</taxonomicName>
: 
<collectionCode id="ED4395980971B22FEF39FBC7235C4E1C" box="[827,855,1051,1077]" country="Russia" name="Paleontological Institute" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">PI</collectionCode>
. 23, fig. 3, 1802: pp. 181, 216 (Indo-Pacific). 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0971B22FE96CFBC7226F4E70" authority=": Smith, 1961: 246" authorityName=": Smith" authorityPageNumber="246" authorityYear="1961" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ambassidae" genus="Ambassis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="37" pageNumber="488" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gymnocephalus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0971B22FE96CFBC7219A4E70" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Ambassis gymnocephalus</emphasis>
: Smith, 1961: 246
</taxonomicName>
; Hill, 1966: 22; Winterbottom, 1976: 62.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF2D5DD50971B22FEC95F94524094C99" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541657" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6541657" box="[151,1026,1689,1713]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6541657/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="488" startId="37.[151,250,1689,1713]" targetBox="[152,1436,1137,1665]" targetPageId="37">
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0971B22FEC95F94524094C99" blockId="37.[151,1026,1689,1713]" box="[151,1026,1689,1713]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0971B22FEC95F945212B4C98" bold="true" box="[151,288,1689,1713]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">FIGURE 44.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0971B22FED24F94522214C98" authorityName=": Smith" authorityYear="1961" box="[294,554,1689,1713]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ambassidae" genus="Ambassis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="37" pageNumber="488" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gymnocephalus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0971B22FED24F94522214C98" box="[294,554,1689,1713]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Ambassis gymnocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a new fish record for the Oman inland waters.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0971B22FECC5F90323AF4D87" blockId="37.[151,1437,1759,2038]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0971B22FECC5F90321AF4CD0" bold="true" box="[199,420,1759,1785]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Short description:</emphasis>
A large deep-bodied glassfish, with a relatively small head, dorsal-fin rays VIll, 8–10; anal-fin rays III, 8–10; pectoral-fin rays 14–15; lateral line interrupted, with 12–13 pored scales + 12–13; gill rakers (8–10) + (22–25); 2 rows of cheek scales. Supraorbital spines 1–5 (usually 3 or 4, 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0971B22FE83BF8FB24764D68" box="[1081,1149,1831,1857]" name="Oman" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Oman</collectingCountry>
specimens 2 or 3); lower edge and angle of preopercle serrate; preopercle ridge completely serrate along lower limb; a large retrorse spine on preorbital just below anterior nostril; preorbital ridge smooth or serrate; interopercle smooth except for 1 or (rarely) 2 small spines. A row of minute teeth on vomer, palatines and tongue.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0971B22FECC5F86B246D4DDC" blockId="37.[151,1437,1759,2038]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0971B22FECC5F86B21CD4DF8" bold="true" box="[199,454,1975,2001]" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">General distribution:</emphasis>
Indo-West Pacific: East and 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0971B22FEF0FF86B23974DF8" box="[781,924,1975,2001]" name="South Africa" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">South Africa</collectingCountry>
east to 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0971B22FEFF1F86B247A4DF8" box="[1011,1137,1975,2001]" name="Philippines" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Philippines</collectingCountry>
and New 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0971B22FE8E7F86B25324DF8" box="[1253,1337,1975,2001]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Guinea</collectingCountry>
, north to 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0971B22FEC95F80720E74DDC" box="[151,236,2011,2037]" name="Taiwan" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, south to Cairns (
<collectingRegion id="4996C3BF0971B22FEDADF80722334DDC" box="[431,568,2011,2037]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Queensland</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0971B22FEE40F80722A54DDF" box="[578,686,2011,2038]" name="Australia" pageId="37" pageNumber="488">Australia</collectingCountry>
). Habitat: freshwater, brackish, marine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3485ED60972B22CECC5FF4A22734B69" pageId="38" pageNumber="489" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0972B22CECC5FF4A21CD4AFC" blockId="38.[151,1436,150,320]" pageId="38" pageNumber="489">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0972B22CECC5FF4A21DE4A99" bold="true" box="[199,469,150,176]" pageId="38" pageNumber="489">
Distribution in 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0972B22CED83FF4A21DB4A99" box="[385,464,150,176]" name="Oman" pageId="38" pageNumber="489">Oman</collectingCountry>
:
</emphasis>
Al Bahayes, 
<collectingRegion id="4996C3BF0972B22CEE72FF4B235C4A99" box="[624,855,150,177]" country="Oman" name="Masqat" pageId="38" pageNumber="489">Muscat Governorate</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation id="136911D80972B22CEF65FF4A23B64A98" box="[871,957,150,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 45" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1494,1518]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,344,1470]" captionTargetId="figure-80@38.[151,1436,344,1470]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 45. Distribution map of Ambassis gymnocephalus in Oman. Pink: Southwestern Arabian Coast, green: Oman Mountains, and yellow: Arabian Interior." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541659" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6541659/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="489">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
). It is a richly vegetated Wadi, adjusted to the Oman Sea coastal area.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0972B22CECC5FF02248C4AD0" blockId="38.[151,1436,150,320]" box="[199,1159,222,249]" pageId="38" pageNumber="489">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0972B22CECC5FF0221364AD1" bold="true" box="[199,317,222,248]" pageId="38" pageNumber="489">Remarks:</emphasis>
